<div class="row">
  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading-l heading--box-blue">Set your goals</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        Setting yourself goals means you’ll know exactly what you want to get out of the day.
      </p>

      <p>
        It’s one of the most important things you can do to make sure you’re clear on your next steps. You might want to know:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>what the application process involves</li>
        <li>which training courses are available and the entry requirements</li>
        <li>how to decide which subject you’ll teach</li>
        <li>if you know which age group you want to teach</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading-l heading--box-blue">Sort your questions</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        Sorting out which questions you want to ask means you’ll be prepared to get the right answers from the right experts.
      </p>

      <p>
        You may have sorted some already. If not, here are a few to get you started.
      <p>

      <p>You could ask teachers:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>how they built their confidence in the classroom</li>
        <li>what they enjoy most about the job</li>
        <li>how they juggle teaching with home life</li>
      </ul>

      <p>You could ask teacher training advisers:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>about the different routes into teaching</li>
        <li>about the funding options available</li>
        <li>to review your personal statement</li>
      </ul>

      <p>You could ask training providers:<p>
      <ul>
        <li>what a typical training term is like</li>
        <li>how much time would be spent in school or on academic learning</li>
        <li>how trainees are assessed with exams and coursework</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading-l heading--box-blue">Shape your day</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        Shaping your day now will help you work out the best way to spend your time.
      </p>

      <p>
         We recommend you start by attending a presentation.
      </p>
      <p>
      The following two presentations take place every hour through the day. They’ll give you lots of food for thought when you chat to our experts.
      </p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong> An introduction to teacher training </strong> is ideal if you want to explore your training options. You’ll get an overview of everything you need to know about the training process.</li>
        <li><strong>Ready to apply </strong> is great if you’ve decided to apply for training and want guidance on the application process.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

<section class="col col-720">
    <h2 class="heading-l heading--box-blue">Where to find the experts</h2>

    <div class="inset">
      <p>
        From teachers to teacher training advisers and training providers, here is where to find the people who will help you take the next step into teaching:
      </p>

      <h3>Teachers</h3>

      <p>
        Find them in the Teacher Hub and discover what teaching is really like.
      </p>
      <p>
        Have one-to-one conversations and group discussions with teachers from primary and secondary schools specialising in a range of subjects.
      </p>

      <h3>Teacher training advisers</h3>

      <p>
        Find them in the Advice Zone and the Funding Zone.
      </p>
      <p>
        Speak to people with years of experience who specialise in supporting people on their journey into teaching.
      </p>

      <h3>Teacher training providers</h3>
      <p>
        Find them in the Provider Zone to chat about training courses and entry requirements.
      </p>

      <h3>Event staff</h3>
      <p> Our friendly team will be there to welcome you at the door. Ask them about the event or eligibility of overseas qualifications.
    </div>
  </section>

